---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "About HomeProjectHub";
const description = "HomeProjectHub provides free, open-source construction calculators for homeowners and DIY builders. Our tools use deterministic formulas with worked examples and common mistakes.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6">
    <header class="border-b border-neutral-100 dark:border-neutral-800 pb-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50 mb-2">About HomeProjectHub</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
      <p>HomeProjectHub is a free collection of professional construction calculators built for homeowners, DIY builders, and small contractors. We focus on two material families where precision matters most: concrete and roofing.</p>

      <p>Every calculator on this site uses deterministic, open-source mathematical formulas. We show you the exact formula, a worked example, and the common mistakes that lead to over- or under-ordering. You can verify every number before you spend money on materials.</p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-2">What Makes Us Different</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
          <li><strong>Save your dimensions:</strong> Enter your room, slab, or roof dimensions once and reuse them across every calculator. No re-typing.</li>
          <li><strong>Compare materials:</strong> Our comparison matrix shows you concrete vs pavers vs gravel side-by-side with durability, maintenance, and lifespan ratings.</li>
          <li><strong>Imperial and metric:</strong> Every calculator supports both unit systems with instant conversion.</li>
          <li><strong>Complete material lists:</strong> Beyond the primary material, we estimate fasteners, underlayment, accessories, and waste so you can order everything in one trip.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-2">Our Calculators</h2>
        <p class="mb-2"><strong>Concrete:</strong> Slab, Footing, Steps, Column, Wall, Tube Form</p>
        <p><strong>Roofing:</strong> Shingles, Metal Panels, Plywood Deck, Pitch</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-2">Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>Our calculators provide estimates for informational purposes only. Always consult a licensed contractor or structural engineer before beginning any construction project. See our <a href="/terms/" class="underline hover:text-neutral-900 dark:hover:text-neutral-100">Terms of Service</a> for details.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
